description:
In 2017, NOAA’s National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI) developed an integrated bathymetric–topographic digital elevation model of Grenada. The 1 arc-second DEM of Grenada covers approximately 28,000 sq. km of the Windward Islands of the Lesser Antilles including St. Vincent, the Grenadines, Petite Martinique, Carriacou, and Grenada. 
Dataset: https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/metadata/geoportal/rest/metadata/item/gov.noaa.ngdc.mgg.dem:11526/html
keywords: CARIBE-EWS, Digital elevation Model, Caribbean, Grenada, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines
name: Grenada DEM extent (footprint)
